<paragraph id="8BE7DF38FFA1FF8CFF6900CF256CFD47" blockId="2.[136,1452,445,760]" pageId="2" pageNumber="227">
<emphasis id="B92C032AFFA1FF8CFF6900CF215BFE43" bold="true" box="[189,256,482,508]" pageId="2" pageNumber="227">Notes</emphasis>
:— 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC9A2C9FFA1FF8CFEF500CF2276FE43" author="Wight, R. &amp; Arnott, G. A. W." box="[289,557,482,508]" pageId="2" pageNumber="227" pagination="263 - 264" refId="ref3091" refString="Wight, R. &amp; Arnott, G. A. W. (1834) Prodromous Florae Peninsulae Indiae Orientalis. Neill &amp; Co, London, pp. 263 - 264." type="book chapter" year="1834">Wight &amp; Arnott (1834)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName id="4C58A4BBFFA1FF8CFD7F00CF23D5FE43" authorityName="Wight &amp; Arnott" authorityYear="1834" box="[683,910,482,508]" class="Globothalamea" family="Millettiidae" genus="Millettia" kingdom="Chromista" order="Rotaliida" pageId="2" pageNumber="227" phylum="Foraminifera" rank="species" species="rubiginosa">
<emphasis id="B92C032AFFA1FF8CFD7F00CF23D5FE43" box="[683,910,482,508]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="227">Millettia rubiginosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on the collections of Wight (
<emphasis id="B92C032AFFA1FF8CFAF900CF25F9FE43" box="[1325,1442,482,508]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="227">Wight 912</emphasis>
) from Courtallum in south 
<collectingCountry id="F34F9FA8FFA1FF8CFE7F032B21B3FD9F" box="[427,488,518,544]" name="India" pageId="2" pageNumber="227">India</collectingCountry>
. Pertaining to the type specification provided in protologue, 
<specimenCount id="9D5E14B1FFA1FF8CFB58032B257FFD9F" box="[1164,1316,518,544]" pageId="2" pageNumber="227" type="generic">13 specimens</specimenCount>
were traced in various herbaria across the globe. Robert Wight was an assistant surgeon and botanist in the service of East 
<collectingCountry id="F34F9FA8FFA1FF8CFAA6030725F7FDFB" box="[1394,1452,554,580]" name="India" pageId="2" pageNumber="227">India</collectingCountry>
Company in Madras and served as superintendent of Madras Botanic Garden during 1826–1828. He returned to 
<collectingCountry id="F34F9FA8FFA1FF8CFF5C035F20BEFD33" box="[136,229,626,652]" name="United Kingdom" pageId="2" pageNumber="227">England</collectingCountry>
on a three-years furlough due to physical problems and spent most of this period in 
<collectingRegion id="499C11DAFFA1FF8CFB64035F257DFD33" box="[1200,1318,626,652]" country="United Kingdom" name="City of Edinburgh" pageId="2" pageNumber="227">Edinburgh</collectingRegion>
to work on his material for the 
<taxonomicName id="4C58A4BBFFA1FF8CFEB703BB2224FD0F" authority="(Basak 1981)" baseAuthorityName="Basak" baseAuthorityYear="1981" box="[355,639,662,688]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Prodromus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="227" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
Prodromus (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC9A2C9FFA1FF8CFE3903BB222DFD0F" author="Basak, R. K." box="[493,630,662,688]" pageId="2" pageNumber="227" pagination="784 - 793" refId="ref2235" refString="Basak, R. K. (1981) Robert Wight and his botanical studies in India. Taxon 30 (4): 784 - 793. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 1220080" type="journal article" year="1981">Basak 1981</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. G.A.W. Arnott was a botanist and Professor of Botany in the University of 
<collectingRegion id="499C11DAFFA1FF8CFF7303972150FD6B" box="[167,267,698,724]" country="United Kingdom" name="Glasgow City" pageId="2" pageNumber="227">Glasgow</collectingRegion>
from 1845 to 1868. The specimens housed at E and K must have been used by the authors to describe 
<taxonomicName id="4C58A4BBFFA1FF8CFA590396215AFD47" authorityName="Wight &amp; Arnott" authorityYear="1834" class="Globothalamea" family="Millettiidae" genus="Millettia" kingdom="Chromista" order="Rotaliida" pageId="2" pageNumber="227" phylum="Foraminifera" rank="species" species="rubiginosa">
<emphasis id="B92C032AFFA1FF8CFA590396215AFD47" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="227">M. rubiginosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Of these, K000848706 is designated here as the 
<typeStatus id="54E3619AFFA1FF8CFCF803F323C8FD47" box="[812,915,734,760]" pageId="2" pageNumber="227">lectotype</typeStatus>
as it agrees well with the protologue.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
